1
00:00:00,840 --> 00:00:04,833
Alright! Before we all get busy later
with Bake Hause of U’s opening,

2
00:00:05,145 --> 00:00:10,241
I just want to thank,
first and foremost, our MVPs…

3
00:00:10,531 --> 00:00:13,018
Oh, you’re so sweet to us, Ate Cha!

4
00:00:13,043 --> 00:00:15,330
That was for us?
Awww, that’s heartwarming!

5
00:00:15,594 --> 00:00:19,681
These two did not forsake us,
especially when we needed them the most…

6
00:00:19,724 --> 00:00:21,208
Of course, we’re not going
to just leave you hanging,

7
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:22,806
who else is bound to
help each other, but us?

8
00:00:23,939 --> 00:00:25,279
What’s are friends are fors?

9
00:00:26,493 --> 00:00:31,965
Our life angels who are
both our pride and joy…

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,320
Angels, she said Angels!
That’s too kind, Ate Cha!

11
00:00:34,345 --> 00:00:35,567
Group hug!

12
00:00:35,592 --> 00:00:38,313
Wait, wait, wait!

13
00:00:40,256 --> 00:00:42,216
I said wait! You two aren’t the MVPs!

14
00:00:42,241 --> 00:00:44,780
- Then who?!
- We’ll thank you later!

15
00:00:45,114 --> 00:00:52,035
The MVPs that we’re talking about
are our kids Atasha and Andres.

16
00:00:52,879 --> 00:00:56,059
If it weren’t for your help,
we wouldn’t have come this far.

17
00:00:56,084 --> 00:00:57,683
So thank you, thank you very much.

18
00:00:58,260 --> 00:00:59,260
You guys are the best!

19
00:00:59,477 --> 00:01:02,934
Dad! That sounded so good to hear!

20
00:01:04,347 --> 00:01:05,980
You’re too nice!

21
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:09,226
Look, there are tears in Andres’ eyes!

22
00:01:09,251 --> 00:01:10,948
Hey, you can’t blot!

23
00:01:10,973 --> 00:01:13,633
But jokes aside, you’ve really changed
and have come so far!

24
00:01:13,753 --> 00:01:14,753
Me?!

25
00:01:15,022 --> 00:01:16,022
Why–when did I ever doubt you?

26
00:01:16,745 --> 00:01:19,957
I’ve trusted you
since the beginning.

27
00:01:19,982 --> 00:01:22,033
- He’s right.
- Oh, you know what I’m talking about.

28
00:01:23,736 --> 00:01:29,184
You are the best! You call the shots
and I always approve your requests!

29
00:01:29,542 --> 00:01:30,542
Wait a second, Dad.

30
00:01:31,505 --> 00:01:34,092
Did you really forget,
or is it selective memory?

31
00:01:34,117 --> 00:01:35,117
Huh?!

32
00:01:36,308 --> 00:01:37,448
Here’s what happened.

33
00:02:39,312 --> 00:02:40,839
So, the idea is,

34
00:02:40,940 --> 00:02:43,727
we’re gonna make a weekly event

35
00:02:44,013 --> 00:02:48,421
so we can develop a habit
out of our customers, okay?

36
00:02:48,597 --> 00:02:49,597
For example,

37
00:02:49,916 --> 00:02:53,496
every Sundays could be
Senior Bonding Day!

38
00:02:53,759 --> 00:02:55,211
- Perfect!
- That’s a good idea!

39
00:02:55,236 --> 00:02:56,236
Exactly!

40
00:02:56,261 --> 00:02:59,152
We can offer free coffee
and free tables for seniors,

41
00:02:59,177 --> 00:03:02,317
and we’ll also encourage them to
buy bread along with their coffee!

42
00:03:02,752 --> 00:03:04,839
- That’s excellent! So great!
- Yeah, we can do that…

43
00:03:05,312 --> 00:03:08,719
but it’s too risky.

44
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,080
Hmm?

45
00:03:10,105 --> 00:03:11,725
Okay? Well, how about this–

46
00:03:12,698 --> 00:03:14,947
speed dating event!

47
00:03:14,972 --> 00:03:16,266
That’s nice, too!

48
00:03:16,318 --> 00:03:19,912
All they need to do is buy
one ensaymada, Isn’t it?!

49
00:03:20,439 --> 00:03:24,604
and they get to pick and choose their date!
It’s a match!

50
00:03:24,794 --> 00:03:26,667
That’s really nice, Tash!

51
00:03:27,253 --> 00:03:28,720
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

52
00:03:28,745 --> 00:03:30,324
You like that?

53
00:03:32,601 --> 00:03:35,128
We’re not a dating site, are we?

54
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:40,369
I just don’t think I like the idea of
people coming to our bake shop for a date,

55
00:03:40,549 --> 00:03:43,595
and then…
it just doesn’t make sense for me.

56
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:47,139
What’s important for me,

57
00:03:47,667 --> 00:03:49,699
more than the gimmick,
is for us to think

58
00:03:49,723 --> 00:03:52,112
about how we’re going
to improve our products.

59
00:03:52,504 --> 00:03:53,650
More than the gimmick.

60
00:03:54,272 --> 00:03:55,272
The gimmick part is good,

61
00:03:55,285 --> 00:03:56,771
of course, but we have to
focus on our products first.

62
00:03:56,796 --> 00:03:58,787
I mean it would mean nothing if
we did have gimmicks in place,

63
00:03:58,811 --> 00:04:01,183
but the products are garbage.

64
00:04:01,894 --> 00:04:02,894
Am I right?

65
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:06,479
You’ve shot all my suggestions, Dad.

66
00:04:06,512 --> 00:04:09,499
No, Tash. What I’m thinking
about is the practicality of it all.

67
00:04:09,780 --> 00:04:11,580
Our system is working just fine.

68
00:04:11,849 --> 00:04:14,895
Oh, it is?

69
00:04:15,676 --> 00:04:17,491
Then why did we come
home in the first place,

70
00:04:17,516 --> 00:04:19,843
if nobody’s going to listen
to us anyway, then?

71
00:04:47,874 --> 00:04:48,874
Tash,

72
00:04:51,477 --> 00:04:53,184
- are you okay?
- Not really!

73
00:04:53,810 --> 00:04:54,810
Not really?

74
00:04:55,510 --> 00:04:56,790
You saw how Dad was in there!

75
00:04:57,097 --> 00:04:59,257
He shot all my suggestions!

76
00:04:59,524 --> 00:05:01,257
Do you know how hard
I worked for that?

77
00:05:02,227 --> 00:05:04,876
- I know, Tash.
- Our efforts have all gone to waste.

78
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:09,041
I agree with you.
But, you know…

79
00:05:09,201 --> 00:05:10,201
Oh gosh, here we go.

80
00:05:11,030 --> 00:05:12,030
Hey, Lola!

81
00:05:12,673 --> 00:05:13,860
You know what, my grandchildren,

82
00:05:15,362 --> 00:05:16,722
I’ve been eavesdropping on you.

83
00:05:19,118 --> 00:05:20,718
Maybe you can just
wanna have pasencia?

84
00:05:21,144 --> 00:05:22,144
No, Lola!

85
00:05:22,286 --> 00:05:24,919
My patience for Dad has run out!

86
00:05:25,423 --> 00:05:27,110
No, what I mean is,

87
00:05:27,409 --> 00:05:29,762
have some pasencia… the biscuit.

88
00:05:30,535 --> 00:05:32,542
Eat some merienda, join me!

89
00:05:32,741 --> 00:05:33,741
Okay.

90
00:05:36,042 --> 00:05:37,469
This pasensya is so good.

91
00:05:38,804 --> 00:05:39,804
You know what, Lola,

92
00:05:40,576 --> 00:05:42,170
the only reason why I’ve
become so upset with Dad

93
00:05:42,515 --> 00:05:44,735
is because we put
our careers abroad

94
00:05:45,128 --> 00:05:46,395
on hold to help them out here.

95
00:05:46,985 --> 00:05:48,523
And then in the end,
it seems like we’re useless,

96
00:05:48,547 --> 00:05:50,472
because only he can call the shots.
So, what’s the point?

97
00:05:50,762 --> 00:05:52,949
Don’t stress yourself out.

98
00:05:53,429 --> 00:05:56,449
Extend your patience
towards your Dad.

99
00:05:56,575 --> 00:05:58,041
What I mean is,

100
00:05:58,130 --> 00:06:00,903
find something to be busy over

101
00:06:00,971 --> 00:06:06,565
so your brains can rest and take a break
from all the problems you’re facing.

102
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:09,023
You know what, Lola, you’re right.

103
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:12,280
And Dad won’t be able to stop me.

104
00:06:12,679 --> 00:06:13,932
From now on,

105
00:06:14,338 --> 00:06:16,192
I will go on with my life.

106
00:06:16,640 --> 00:06:19,140
Thank you, Lola, you’re the best.
We love you!

107
00:06:19,670 --> 00:06:20,790
Love you too, my granddaughter!

108
00:06:21,201 --> 00:06:23,141
You know what, Lola, me too.

109
00:06:23,166 --> 00:06:25,598
I’m gonna find something
to be busy over!

110
00:06:25,982 --> 00:06:26,982
That’s right!

111
00:06:27,515 --> 00:06:28,515
Thank you, Lola!

112
00:06:30,132 --> 00:06:32,995
Hey! Hey!
Look at you two!

113
00:06:33,237 --> 00:06:34,877
You took everything!

114
00:06:35,197 --> 00:06:36,750
That was too much,
give me some!

115
00:06:45,618 --> 00:06:46,618
Tasha!

116
00:06:47,095 --> 00:06:48,095
Where are you headed?

117
00:06:49,168 --> 00:06:50,168
I’m leaving.

118
00:06:50,888 --> 00:06:51,888
You’re running away?

119
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:55,627
No, I meant I’m going out,
as in just going out and coming home later.

120
00:06:55,690 --> 00:06:57,210
Oh, okay.

121
00:06:57,810 --> 00:06:58,810
Hang on one second,

122
00:06:59,278 --> 00:07:02,558
you still haven’t spoken to your
Daddy since last night, have you?

123
00:07:03,166 --> 00:07:04,340
Leave him be.

124
00:07:05,734 --> 00:07:07,841
I’ll just go on a date.

125
00:07:08,340 --> 00:07:09,340
Date?

126
00:07:09,687 --> 00:07:10,687
What date?

127
00:07:10,886 --> 00:07:12,419
It’s just a lunch date, Ma.

128
00:07:12,817 --> 00:07:13,817
Lunch date?!

129
00:07:13,842 --> 00:07:14,921
Lunch! Just lunch!

130
00:07:26,742 --> 00:07:27,742
Tash!

131
00:07:27,905 --> 00:07:30,505
Gotta go. My date is here.

132
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:31,530
Atasha?

133
00:07:32,226 --> 00:07:33,500
Nice to see you!

134
00:07:33,575 --> 00:07:34,575
Let’s go?

135
00:07:36,456 --> 00:07:37,456
My love!

136
00:07:38,090 --> 00:07:39,090
My love!

137
00:07:40,025 --> 00:07:41,977
- My love!
- My love!

138
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:44,892
- My love!
- Yes?! What’s happening?!

139
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:46,394
I think my head is spinning.

140
00:07:46,570 --> 00:07:49,612
Your head is spinning? Come here.
Here, stay close, sit here.

141
00:07:49,701 --> 00:07:51,658
- I think I’m about to collapse.
- Why are you going to collapse?!

142
00:07:51,683 --> 00:07:53,363
You need to catch me!

143
00:07:53,436 --> 00:07:56,009
- Why?!
- Because… I think I… wait a minute.

144
00:07:56,182 --> 00:07:57,182
What happened?

145
00:07:57,207 --> 00:08:04,088
Atasha is having a
May-December love affair!

146
00:08:10,462 --> 00:08:11,575
Wow, Orb!

147
00:08:12,365 --> 00:08:14,832
You look like a mature guy
reading the newspaper!

148
00:08:15,983 --> 00:08:19,362
Oh, this? I’m just looking for a sideline
so I have something

149
00:08:20,114 --> 00:08:22,981
to be busy with rather
than just the bakery.

150
00:08:23,440 --> 00:08:25,660
Are you an old person?

151
00:08:26,572 --> 00:08:28,799
You do know that the
internet exists, don’t you?

152
00:08:29,218 --> 00:08:30,978
It’s easier to do your search there.

153
00:08:31,797 --> 00:08:33,971
Hey, look! A cute dog!

154
00:08:34,321 --> 00:08:35,348
Hey, no, wait!

155
00:08:35,373 --> 00:08:36,930
Look at it, it’s so cute!

156
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:38,327
I’m sorry, excuse me.

157
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,251
Excuse us, sorry!

158
00:08:42,046 --> 00:08:43,166
Hello!

159
00:08:43,191 --> 00:08:44,191
Look, it’s so cute!

160
00:08:44,389 --> 00:08:46,702
Let’s ask around,
maybe someone here knows this dog.

161
00:08:47,009 --> 00:08:48,683
- Alright, let’s go?
- Let’s go, let’s go!

162
00:08:48,708 --> 00:08:50,063
- Kuya Chard!
- Yeah, Andres?

163
00:08:50,088 --> 00:08:52,674
Do you know anyone
who possibly has a dog this breed?

164
00:08:53,538 --> 00:08:55,258
I don’t, sorry!

165
00:08:55,646 --> 00:08:56,946
But that’s a cute dog!

166
00:08:56,971 --> 00:08:58,272
- Isn’t it?!
- It’s so cute!

167
00:08:58,297 --> 00:08:59,297
It looks so cute!

168
00:08:59,432 --> 00:09:00,759
Aww, poor dog!

169
00:09:00,980 --> 00:09:02,827
- Are you missing?
- It looks expensive!

170
00:09:02,858 --> 00:09:04,735
- Are you lost?
- I know this breed!

171
00:09:06,078 --> 00:09:10,124
Oh my gosh! My puppy! Baby!

172
00:09:10,156 --> 00:09:14,245
I’ve been looking all over for you!

173
00:09:14,270 --> 00:09:15,330
This is yours, Ate Mariposa?

174
00:09:15,367 --> 00:09:17,033
Yeah, it’s mine!

175
00:09:17,058 --> 00:09:19,164
Nope, nope, nope, nope!

176
00:09:19,779 --> 00:09:21,206
Do not trust her!

177
00:09:21,827 --> 00:09:24,360
She’s just gonna sell that pup,
just like how she sells her phone!

178
00:09:24,847 --> 00:09:26,553
- Oh!
- Of course, not!

179
00:09:26,717 --> 00:09:28,710
That’s expensi… I mean

180
00:09:28,735 --> 00:09:30,368
I love this pup!

181
00:09:31,101 --> 00:09:35,534
If you really are a dog lover,
prove it to us–is it a boy or a girl?

182
00:09:35,707 --> 00:09:37,244
- Alright, tell us!
- Um, uh, um…it’s a…

183
00:09:37,269 --> 00:09:38,816
- Girl or boy?
- A boy!

184
00:09:38,841 --> 00:09:41,397
- He’s a boy! My baby is a boy!
- Is it a boy, Andres?

185
00:09:42,739 --> 00:09:44,665
Mariposa, she’s a girl!

186
00:09:44,690 --> 00:09:46,744
See, I told you.

187
00:09:46,977 --> 00:09:48,023
You know what,
let’s just do it this way.

188
00:09:48,166 --> 00:09:51,856
You may leave the pup here,
because it got lost here.

189
00:09:52,293 --> 00:09:54,100
The owner will, hopefully,
come looking for her here.

190
00:09:54,164 --> 00:09:55,323
That would be better
so I can get the reward.

191
00:09:55,348 --> 00:09:59,626
I mean the owner can get the pup!

192
00:09:59,822 --> 00:10:02,699
Oh, no, thanks,
Boss Beauty, but it looks like

193
00:10:02,723 --> 00:10:05,470
Andres and I will be
taking care of her,

194
00:10:06,236 --> 00:10:08,303
since she looks like
she’s harmless.

195
00:10:10,157 --> 00:10:11,157
Whatever.

196
00:10:11,787 --> 00:10:12,787
Let’s go.

197
00:10:13,842 --> 00:10:14,882
Bye-bye!

198
00:10:15,288 --> 00:10:17,555
Take good care of that dog!
That’s expensive!

199
00:10:17,755 --> 00:10:19,388
Keep the reward in mind!

200
00:10:33,494 --> 00:10:34,494
Hey, you two!

201
00:10:34,724 --> 00:10:38,577
Why do you look like
you’ve been fighting?

202
00:10:40,701 --> 00:10:42,987
Are you finally
on your way to separating?

203
00:10:44,193 --> 00:10:45,653
You know what, BFF,

204
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:48,652
sometimes, the longer you wait,
the more painful it is.

205
00:10:49,154 --> 00:10:50,694
If I were you,
I’d make a decision right away.

206
00:10:52,766 --> 00:10:54,626
You talk too much.

207
00:10:55,012 --> 00:10:56,012
Wh–why?

208
00:10:56,785 --> 00:10:57,805
I have a problem.

209
00:10:57,830 --> 00:10:58,849
We’re not fighting.

210
00:10:58,874 --> 00:11:00,966
I have a problem,
because my daughter Atasha…

211
00:11:03,212 --> 00:11:06,033
she’s on a date
with someone much older than she is.

212
00:11:07,470 --> 00:11:08,470
What?

213
00:11:09,370 --> 00:11:10,370
Well,

214
00:11:11,622 --> 00:11:15,375
at least now you know what it feels
like when a woman is taken from you.

215
00:11:18,729 --> 00:11:19,754
What?

216
00:11:19,779 --> 00:11:21,590
Hey! Talking to yourself is
not gonna get you anywhere.

217
00:11:21,960 --> 00:11:22,960
Go and have yourself checked.

218
00:11:23,106 --> 00:11:24,106
Me?

219
00:11:24,313 --> 00:11:25,313
Hang on,

220
00:11:25,323 --> 00:11:26,510
it’s already six o’ clock,

221
00:11:27,025 --> 00:11:28,379
and your daughter still
hasn’t made it home.

222
00:11:28,659 --> 00:11:31,931
Look what you did,
Atasha is rebelling because of you.

223
00:11:33,929 --> 00:11:36,514
What do you mean she's rebelling
because of me? How is this my fault?

224
00:11:36,539 --> 00:11:38,119
Wasn’t she supposed
to say sorry to me?

225
00:11:41,551 --> 00:11:42,551
Hey!

226
00:11:42,824 --> 00:11:45,463
Mom, Dad, this is Eddie!

227
00:11:46,336 --> 00:11:47,336
Hi!

228
00:11:50,341 --> 00:11:51,401
My love, can you scooch over a bit?

229
00:11:51,426 --> 00:11:52,426
Calm down.

230
00:11:52,852 --> 00:11:54,692
Wait…
Tash, your Daddy?

231
00:11:55,338 --> 00:11:57,151
Hi, Daddy!

232
00:11:57,206 --> 00:11:58,420
What do you mean, Daddy?!

233
00:11:58,593 --> 00:12:00,986
- I’m just being polite.
- Why would you call me Daddy?!

234
00:12:01,011 --> 00:12:02,011
Because you’re a Dad!

235
00:12:03,307 --> 00:12:04,580
Don’t you laugh at me!

236
00:12:04,605 --> 00:12:06,742
- Daddy! Old guy!
- Um, hi.

237
00:12:08,461 --> 00:12:09,601
Let me get your blessing, grandpa.

238
00:12:09,813 --> 00:12:10,813
Did you just call me grandpa?

239
00:12:10,866 --> 00:12:12,684
- There you go, see!
- I’m gonna cripple this guy!

240
00:12:12,709 --> 00:12:14,060
- I told you!
- Try and stop me!

241
00:12:14,085 --> 00:12:17,595
No, stop, don’t rush into it!

242
00:12:17,682 --> 00:12:18,902
Ah, Eddie,

243
00:12:19,284 --> 00:12:21,510
do you want some milk?
For your osteoporosis?

244
00:12:23,081 --> 00:12:27,108
Ah, you don’t have to bother,
I’m not staying long.

245
00:12:27,301 --> 00:12:32,474
I just met with Tasha for my proposal.

246
00:12:32,499 --> 00:12:34,742
- Proposal?!
- Yes, that’s why I’m wooing her.

247
00:12:34,915 --> 00:12:35,915
Wooing?!

248
00:12:36,562 --> 00:12:37,762
- He’s wooing her?!
- Isn’t that right?

249
00:12:38,405 --> 00:12:40,220
Oh, god, I can’t breathe.

250
00:12:40,245 --> 00:12:41,452
My chest is tightening.

251
00:12:41,522 --> 00:12:42,522
Relax, relax.

252
00:12:42,547 --> 00:12:43,606
Are you okay, Dad?

253
00:12:43,656 --> 00:12:46,050
Do not call me Dad!
Do not touch me either!

254
00:12:46,144 --> 00:12:47,144
Hoo!

255
00:12:47,169 --> 00:12:49,263
My love, my love, I’m fine.
I’m okay, I’m fine.

256
00:12:49,288 --> 00:12:50,849
- Okay.
- Sorry, I was just caught off guard.

257
00:12:50,874 --> 00:12:54,079
Why didn’t you tell me sooner
that you were Atasha’s boss?!

258
00:12:55,206 --> 00:12:59,101
How could I have said that
when you were already freaking out earlier!

259
00:12:59,126 --> 00:13:02,820
And you, why on earth
would you call him by name?!

260
00:13:04,602 --> 00:13:07,934
I’m fine with being called
“Sir” or “Boss”,

261
00:13:07,958 --> 00:13:10,295
because in our company,

262
00:13:10,320 --> 00:13:12,455
I’d like for everyone to
feel that we’re a big family.

263
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:13,480
- Family?!
- Yes, family!

264
00:13:13,505 --> 00:13:14,505
Family!

265
00:13:14,530 --> 00:13:19,333
Anyway,
I’m not yet Tasha’s boss officially.

266
00:13:20,744 --> 00:13:26,902
I’m the head of the Philippine counterpart
of Tasha’s agency in Singapore.

267
00:13:27,335 --> 00:13:30,740
So, I’m “wooing” Tasha

268
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:34,327
so she’ll decide to work for me,
so she won’t go back to Singapore anymore.

269
00:13:34,426 --> 00:13:37,216
Oh, that’s the proposal!

270
00:13:37,241 --> 00:13:38,505
Ow, ow! My chest is acting up again!

271
00:13:38,530 --> 00:13:41,865
I’m really sorry about
how we reacted earlier.

272
00:13:41,890 --> 00:13:46,190
It was a mix up, but you really
can’t blame me as Tasha’s mother.

273
00:13:46,215 --> 00:13:47,695
I was just worried.

274
00:13:47,720 --> 00:13:48,733
God!

275
00:13:49,195 --> 00:13:51,466
- You’re Tasha’s mother?!
- I am!

276
00:13:51,491 --> 00:13:53,536
I thought you were
his eldest daughter!

277
00:13:54,491 --> 00:13:55,865
Oh, stop it.

278
00:13:57,253 --> 00:13:58,639
Okay, here comes your youngest.

279
00:13:58,926 --> 00:14:01,152
- What?
- Lola Max–this is Lola Maxi.

280
00:14:01,205 --> 00:14:02,205
Oh…

281
00:14:03,578 --> 00:14:04,838
- What? Why?
- Do not move!

282
00:14:04,863 --> 00:14:06,157
What?! Is this a stick-up?

283
00:14:06,532 --> 00:14:08,145
Post! And repost!

284
00:14:09,761 --> 00:14:10,761
Roman!

285
00:14:10,806 --> 00:14:12,186
Roman, you’ve come back!

286
00:14:12,211 --> 00:14:13,239
- What did she just say?
- Roman!

287
00:14:13,264 --> 00:14:15,133
Lola Maxi, lola Maxi!

288
00:14:15,326 --> 00:14:17,926
Lola Maxi, no!

289
00:14:18,054 --> 00:14:20,994
Lola Maxi, no!
He’s Tasha’s colleague.

290
00:14:21,134 --> 00:14:23,274
Sorry about that.

291
00:14:23,313 --> 00:14:27,263
But hey look, if you do take a good look,
he really looks like Lolo Roman!

292
00:14:27,359 --> 00:14:28,985
That’s what I’m saying!

293
00:14:29,291 --> 00:14:30,718
Roman is back!

294
00:14:30,998 --> 00:14:33,599
- Roman!
- Lola Maxi! Lola Maxi! Lola Maxi!

295
00:14:33,624 --> 00:14:34,870
Oh wow, your grandmother is obscene.

296
00:14:34,895 --> 00:14:36,304
You’re right! I’m sorry, I’m so sorry.
Give me a moment here.

297
00:14:36,329 --> 00:14:38,350
Eddie, you know what,
you may leave now.

298
00:14:38,970 --> 00:14:41,310
I unfortunately called for back-up.

299
00:14:41,335 --> 00:14:42,868
Back-up?!

300
00:14:42,893 --> 00:14:45,105
No, because I thought
he was courting Atasha,

301
00:14:45,129 --> 00:14:46,615
so of course I called for back-up!

302
00:14:46,699 --> 00:14:49,536
I wanted to scare him off.
Look at his face!

303
00:14:49,561 --> 00:14:51,345
Okay, I’m leaving. I’m leaving now.

304
00:14:51,370 --> 00:14:53,065
You should!
The back-up I called for is arriving,

305
00:14:53,090 --> 00:14:55,010
a riot might ensue
if you don’t leave.

306
00:14:55,035 --> 00:14:57,790
- Oh, my!
- See, I told you, I told you!

307
00:14:57,841 --> 00:14:58,974
Aha! Aha!

308
00:15:01,034 --> 00:15:06,916
So you’re the one who’s been
courting Kuya Aga’s daughter, huh?!

309
00:15:07,269 --> 00:15:11,903
And what if I give you the most bitter no,
while I cripple you?!

310
00:15:12,094 --> 00:15:13,094
Oh!

311
00:15:14,395 --> 00:15:16,581
You’re pissing me off!

312
00:15:16,692 --> 00:15:19,739
Do you want me to bury you
underneath this house?!

313
00:15:23,384 --> 00:15:24,977
Ow! You hit me! I told you to hit me
a bit on the upper end!

314
00:15:25,755 --> 00:15:28,108
That’s what we rehearsed!

315
00:15:29,205 --> 00:15:30,339
I’m sorry, I got carried away.

316
00:15:31,516 --> 00:15:32,809
Come up here, come up.

317
00:15:34,708 --> 00:15:36,175
- Good job!
- Anne!

318
00:15:36,839 --> 00:15:38,205
Why haven’t you closed the bakery yet?

319
00:15:38,809 --> 00:15:39,809
I’m sorry, Tso K.

320
00:15:40,055 --> 00:15:43,368
We’ve just gotten busy with
taking care of this pup we got.

321
00:15:46,467 --> 00:15:48,497
Oh, and she’s wearing bling-bling!

322
00:15:48,675 --> 00:15:49,675
How spoiled!

323
00:15:49,848 --> 00:15:50,848
She’s cute, though!

324
00:15:51,165 --> 00:15:55,211
I’m sure her owner is gonna
give out a huge reward!

325
00:15:56,934 --> 00:15:59,521
Boss Beauty said the same thing.

326
00:16:00,873 --> 00:16:04,156
But if no one tries
to look for it, Tso K,

327
00:16:04,772 --> 00:16:06,772
can we have her stay here?

328
00:16:06,832 --> 00:16:09,464
No! What do you mean
stay here?! No way!

329
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:13,190
Except if it knows
how to knead some dough

330
00:16:13,527 --> 00:16:15,534
or transact with customers,

331
00:16:16,018 --> 00:16:18,438
then maybe! But no, I won’t take in
another mouth to feed in here!

332
00:16:18,933 --> 00:16:19,933
You understand?!

333
00:16:19,958 --> 00:16:21,019
Okay, I’m gonna go inside,
because that might bite me

334
00:16:21,043 --> 00:16:22,079
after what I’ve just said. Bye!

335
00:16:22,952 --> 00:16:23,952
And I said no!

336
00:16:31,953 --> 00:16:32,966
Tso K is fine with it!

337
00:16:34,668 --> 00:16:36,148
It doesn’t sound like
it was ok with him!

338
00:16:37,038 --> 00:16:38,038
Don’t worry, I got this.

339
00:16:38,375 --> 00:16:40,549
Maybe not everyday,
but I got this!

340
00:16:40,801 --> 00:16:44,467
Let’s do it this way, you get her MWF,
then I got her TThS.

341
00:16:44,734 --> 00:16:46,607
And then on Sundays, we switch!

342
00:16:46,906 --> 00:16:49,846
Wow! You’ve got it all
planned out, don’t you?

343
00:16:50,307 --> 00:16:51,996
- Of course, I do!
- But...

344
00:16:52,021 --> 00:16:53,356
what if somebody
comes looking for her?

345
00:16:53,989 --> 00:16:55,469
Let’s not think about that anymore.

346
00:16:55,981 --> 00:16:58,588
What we should be thinking
about is what to name her.

347
00:16:58,794 --> 00:17:01,827
How do you feel about
putting our names together?!

348
00:17:02,644 --> 00:17:06,054
Andres plus Anne equals…?

349
00:17:07,360 --> 00:17:08,780
- An-an!
- An-an!

350
00:17:08,805 --> 00:17:10,066
That’s it!

351
00:17:10,091 --> 00:17:11,271
Sounds great!

352
00:17:11,296 --> 00:17:12,893
That’s really good!
Let’s start calling her that, Orb!

353
00:17:13,665 --> 00:17:14,698
Hello, An-An!

354
00:17:17,491 --> 00:17:18,491
Hello?

355
00:17:18,795 --> 00:17:20,194
- Oh! Roman!
- I’m sorry, Lola Maxi.

356
00:17:20,392 --> 00:17:21,392
I mean…

357
00:17:21,753 --> 00:17:25,786
Lola Maxi, I’m sorry,
I forgot something important.

358
00:17:26,386 --> 00:17:27,786
What is it?

359
00:17:30,125 --> 00:17:31,125
It’s you!

360
00:17:31,997 --> 00:17:34,017
I’m looking for you, Maxi.

361
00:17:35,052 --> 00:17:36,052
I am Roman.

362
00:17:36,161 --> 00:17:38,674
Roman! Oh, don’t be like this!

363
00:17:38,771 --> 00:17:40,691
You know how fragile I can get!

364
00:17:41,497 --> 00:17:44,507
And plus, you have too much clothes on!

365
00:17:44,662 --> 00:17:47,835
I don’t care if you’re fragile,
because I am impulsively passionate!

366
00:17:51,698 --> 00:17:52,698
Roman...

367
00:17:52,871 --> 00:17:54,892
Oh, I love you so–

368
00:17:57,528 --> 00:18:01,853
Lola! Lola! Lola! Lola!
Wake up! Lola! Lola!

369
00:18:03,026 --> 00:18:04,200
You’re so noisy!

370
00:18:04,225 --> 00:18:05,225
Cha!

371
00:18:05,413 --> 00:18:06,539
What is the matter with you?!

372
00:18:07,496 --> 00:18:14,766
You just ruined my dream!
I was dreaming of Eddie!

373
00:18:14,936 --> 00:18:17,613
- We were just about to–
- No, stop!

374
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:20,858
He was already up here!
And then you woke me up!

375
00:18:20,883 --> 00:18:22,286
Wait a second, Lola Maxi.

376
00:18:22,594 --> 00:18:23,594
Eddie?

377
00:18:23,692 --> 00:18:24,998
Why Eddie?

378
00:18:25,578 --> 00:18:27,385
Do you have a crush on Eddie?!

379
00:18:28,683 --> 00:18:31,937
Well, you really can’t blame me, Cha.

380
00:18:32,191 --> 00:18:36,479
You saw how he looks,
he looks exactly like your Lolo Roman!

381
00:18:37,133 --> 00:18:38,133
Oh!

382
00:18:38,158 --> 00:18:45,657
I remember back in the day when we used
to do what we both loved to do at midnight.

383
00:18:46,586 --> 00:18:50,883
Oh gosh, Lola, if that’s an obscene story,
you might as well keep it a secret.

384
00:18:50,941 --> 00:18:52,688
Look at you!
I don’t want to talk to you!

385
00:18:53,398 --> 00:18:55,145
I only want to talk to Roman!

386
00:18:56,411 --> 00:18:57,411
Roman!

387
00:19:05,723 --> 00:19:07,821
Oh, my love!

388
00:19:08,138 --> 00:19:12,145
The coffee isn’t at fault here,
don’t blame it!

389
00:19:12,890 --> 00:19:15,177
And who am I supposed to blame?
Have you seen your daughter Tasha?

390
00:19:15,202 --> 00:19:16,202
Did you see her?

391
00:19:16,227 --> 00:19:18,727
She left again with Eddie,

392
00:19:18,752 --> 00:19:20,526
and didn’t even ask for my permission

393
00:19:21,032 --> 00:19:23,678
Well, you know who
she got it from, don’t you?

394
00:19:23,822 --> 00:19:26,681
You’re both hard-headed!

395
00:19:26,786 --> 00:19:27,799
I’m hard-headed?

396
00:19:27,868 --> 00:19:28,868
Of course you are!

397
00:19:30,041 --> 00:19:31,221
You see, now you see?!

398
00:19:31,738 --> 00:19:33,165
I’ve been telling you!

399
00:19:34,110 --> 00:19:38,663
Cha, now you’re seeing
how my BFF really is…

400
00:19:39,743 --> 00:19:41,410
- What did you just say to her?
- No, I’m just saying,

401
00:19:41,434 --> 00:19:44,319
you’ve got some bad
characteristics, too, BFF!

402
00:19:44,344 --> 00:19:45,578
It’s better I give you
the truth straight!

403
00:19:45,849 --> 00:19:47,076
You’re not so agreeable!

404
00:19:47,453 --> 00:19:48,527
I’m not agreeable?

405
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:49,667
Yeah!

406
00:19:50,246 --> 00:19:52,510
Oh, okay fine.
I trust our daughter, my love.

407
00:19:52,534 --> 00:19:54,384
You know that, don’t you?
It’s true.

408
00:19:55,070 --> 00:19:56,605
But then, when I think about it,
the reality is–it happens!

409
00:19:56,630 --> 00:19:58,410
Sometimes the boss falls in love
with their subordinates!

410
00:19:58,435 --> 00:19:59,435
Ha!

411
00:19:59,612 --> 00:20:00,732
That’s right, Kuya Aga!

412
00:20:01,284 --> 00:20:05,263
You know what! The next minute,
Tash is going to be his girlfriend!

413
00:20:05,288 --> 00:20:06,288
He could be right!

414
00:20:08,021 --> 00:20:11,625
You know what,
it’s the end of the day.

415
00:20:11,964 --> 00:20:13,724
How about we march over there
and cripple the guy?!

416
00:20:13,749 --> 00:20:15,054
- We should!
- Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

417
00:20:15,078 --> 00:20:16,792
- Cripple him, cripple him!
- Hey, you two, hold your horses!

418
00:20:16,817 --> 00:20:17,851
Here she comes!

419
00:20:17,876 --> 00:20:20,453
No one is crippling anyone!

420
00:20:20,752 --> 00:20:21,866
Don’t be war freaks!

421
00:20:22,194 --> 00:20:25,008
That’s right, we’re not people
who hurt people!

422
00:20:25,101 --> 00:20:26,541
- Right, Kuya Dick?!
- That’s right!

423
00:20:28,180 --> 00:20:29,180
But who is Kuya Dick?!

424
00:20:29,940 --> 00:20:31,493
- Tso K!
- Oh, I mean Tso K…

425
00:20:32,468 --> 00:20:33,468
That’s Tso K!

426
00:20:35,583 --> 00:20:40,541
Oh what a lucky dog,
being carried by her owners!

427
00:20:41,348 --> 00:20:43,894
She gets too skittish
when she’s on the ground.

428
00:20:44,222 --> 00:20:47,635
And also she has
such a big appetite!

429
00:20:48,250 --> 00:20:50,943
Aww, you two look like parents!

430
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:53,740
You look so, so sweet!

431
00:20:54,021 --> 00:20:55,021
Oh, I know!

432
00:20:55,036 --> 00:20:59,717
Maybe this is your training ground
when you two finally have your own baby!

433
00:21:00,235 --> 00:21:01,235
Yuck, no!

434
00:21:01,260 --> 00:21:02,320
Oh, there’s butterflies
in my stomach now!

435
00:21:02,345 --> 00:21:03,926
I am horrified!

436
00:21:04,537 --> 00:21:06,234
- Ew!
- There you are!

437
00:21:06,842 --> 00:21:08,539
- There you are!
- Why?

438
00:21:08,564 --> 00:21:11,648
- Okay, I’ll make a deal with you, alright?
- Okay, okay.

439
00:21:11,673 --> 00:21:14,580
Since you found the dog
in front of my house,

440
00:21:14,813 --> 00:21:16,320
let’s split the reward three ways.

441
00:21:16,408 --> 00:21:17,408
Ah, excuse me?

442
00:21:17,433 --> 00:21:18,806
- Reward?
- Three ways, just three ways?

443
00:21:18,830 --> 00:21:20,745
- I’m not –
- Wait, what reward?

444
00:21:20,770 --> 00:21:23,069
Reward! Look at this!

445
00:21:23,357 --> 00:21:27,292
I saw this posted–it’s posted everywhere,
come look! Haven’t you seen this?

446
00:21:27,754 --> 00:21:28,754
There’s one.

447
00:21:29,308 --> 00:21:30,721
Yeah, but that’s not An-An.

448
00:21:31,614 --> 00:21:32,754
That’s not her.

449
00:21:32,779 --> 00:21:34,279
- Isn’t it?
- Let me see!

450
00:21:34,431 --> 00:21:38,585
Oh, it doesn’t look like her.

451
00:21:40,055 --> 00:21:42,335
Oh, this one looks more alike!

452
00:21:42,360 --> 00:21:44,024
Wow, wow, wow!

453
00:21:44,049 --> 00:21:46,186
There, see! Perfect!

454
00:21:46,211 --> 00:21:48,410
- One and the same!
- I’m not the one who looks like it!

455
00:21:48,603 --> 00:21:49,637
It seems like… this…

456
00:21:52,588 --> 00:21:54,395
This one! It looks like this one!

457
00:21:56,462 --> 00:21:58,422
This dog looks like this one!

458
00:21:59,089 --> 00:22:00,903
Ah, really? Me?

459
00:22:01,406 --> 00:22:02,720
- Tso K…
- I look like a dog?

460
00:22:02,993 --> 00:22:04,245
Huh? I look like a dog?

461
00:22:04,368 --> 00:22:05,668
You’re dead!

462
00:22:05,693 --> 00:22:07,340
- No, Tso K…
- You’re dead, Boss Beauty!

463
00:22:07,365 --> 00:22:08,860
Hello, crush!

464
00:22:08,885 --> 00:22:10,650
No, Tso K, I meant me…
I look like this dog.

465
00:22:10,675 --> 00:22:12,335
No, I heard you loud and clear,
I look like a dog?

466
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:13,845
No, I meant me!
I look like this dog, look!

467
00:22:13,985 --> 00:22:14,985
Arf arf!

468
00:22:15,162 --> 00:22:16,668
No, I’m gonna make you my dog!

469
00:22:16,757 --> 00:22:17,757
Sit!

470
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:19,480
Stand!

471
00:22:19,876 --> 00:22:20,876
Roll over!

472
00:22:22,035 --> 00:22:23,062
Ow, that hurt!

473
00:22:23,168 --> 00:22:24,168
Play dead!

474
00:22:44,940 --> 00:22:49,863
Tash, can you please
refuse the offer?

475
00:22:50,815 --> 00:22:51,835
I’ll think about it.

476
00:22:52,853 --> 00:22:53,853
You’ll think about it?

477
00:22:55,216 --> 00:22:57,036
Please, refuse it.

478
00:22:57,067 --> 00:22:59,707
I’m telling you, my gut is feeling
something weird about that guy!

479
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:02,240
Don’t judge him. Look!

480
00:23:02,394 --> 00:23:05,694
He got me this cake,
and he even got me these flowers!

481
00:23:06,003 --> 00:23:07,003
I told you s–see,

482
00:23:07,028 --> 00:23:09,603
the only thing missing there
now is a stuffed teddy bear

483
00:23:09,628 --> 00:23:10,855
and he’s officially
courting you!

484
00:23:10,938 --> 00:23:12,598
He really does have a different
intention towards you!

485
00:23:13,118 --> 00:23:15,331
Is that so hard to understand?!

486
00:23:15,777 --> 00:23:18,090
And I’m just supposed to listen
to what you’re telling me to do,

487
00:23:18,530 --> 00:23:20,507
but when it’s our turn
to suggest anything,

488
00:23:20,532 --> 00:23:21,855
you shoot us down right away?

489
00:23:21,880 --> 00:23:26,086
Okay, just for that,
I’ve decided that I’m accepting the offer.

490
00:23:26,243 --> 00:23:27,570
Do not talk back like that!

491
00:23:27,595 --> 00:23:29,490
You hear me?!
Do not talk back to me like that!

492
00:23:29,673 --> 00:23:31,760
If you’d rather go back to Singapore,
then do it!

493
00:23:31,897 --> 00:23:33,004
Go ahead, and work there!

494
00:23:37,404 --> 00:23:39,158
I would rather you go back there
than accept that offer!

495
00:23:39,392 --> 00:23:41,665
I’ve been telling you
there’s something going on with that guy!

496
00:23:44,980 --> 00:23:46,633
Boss Eddie gave me this

497
00:23:47,217 --> 00:23:52,531
because it’s officially my second year
anniversary with my company in Singapore.

498
00:23:55,141 --> 00:23:56,635
If I were still there, by now,

499
00:23:58,007 --> 00:23:59,174
I would have already been promoted.

500
00:24:00,553 --> 00:24:02,492
But I chose to come home and help you,

501
00:24:03,648 --> 00:24:05,308
but look–it seems like
you’re pushing me away.

502
00:24:06,527 --> 00:24:10,581
Dad, my boss trusts me.

503
00:24:11,778 --> 00:24:15,085
Even more so than you do.

504
00:24:34,381 --> 00:24:35,381
This is not her!

505
00:24:35,411 --> 00:24:36,551
Her color is lighter.

506
00:24:36,576 --> 00:24:37,576
Look!

507
00:24:37,718 --> 00:24:39,617
- She’s lighter!
- Come on, Orb.

508
00:24:39,797 --> 00:24:41,130
The ink is just a little blurry!

509
00:24:41,548 --> 00:24:42,548
This is her.

510
00:24:42,607 --> 00:24:43,607
Really?

511
00:24:43,960 --> 00:24:46,137
So, are we just going
to return her, then?

512
00:24:46,708 --> 00:24:49,408
Of course we are!
We’re not dognapping her!

513
00:24:49,860 --> 00:24:52,300
Oh, dogs go missing everyday!

514
00:24:53,368 --> 00:24:55,241
I’m sure her owners
are gonna be able to move on!

515
00:24:55,308 --> 00:24:56,308
They’re gonna be fine!

516
00:24:57,294 --> 00:24:58,294
Orb, come on.

517
00:24:58,318 --> 00:24:59,318
Don’t assume anything.

518
00:24:59,528 --> 00:25:01,208
If that’s how you’re reacting
over the fact that we’re gonna miss her,

519
00:25:01,721 --> 00:25:05,129
think about her real owners.

520
00:25:06,054 --> 00:25:07,200
Why are you being like this?

521
00:25:08,184 --> 00:25:10,330
Why does it seem so easy for you?

522
00:25:10,657 --> 00:25:11,677
No, it’s not that.

523
00:25:12,101 --> 00:25:13,101
What I’m trying to say is that

524
00:25:14,118 --> 00:25:16,424
even if we had her for
just a short period of time,

525
00:25:16,755 --> 00:25:18,375
we still became a part of her life.

526
00:25:20,331 --> 00:25:22,500
And if she ever goes missing again,

527
00:25:23,059 --> 00:25:26,070
at least she’ll know that
there are people like us

528
00:25:26,493 --> 00:25:27,900
who are willing to take
care of strays like her.

529
00:25:28,586 --> 00:25:30,946
So, let’s just be happy, okay?

530
00:25:33,988 --> 00:25:34,988
An-An!

531
00:25:37,293 --> 00:25:38,293
An-An, come here.

532
00:25:42,876 --> 00:25:44,723
Do you wanna leave Mommy and Daddy?

533
00:25:45,629 --> 00:25:46,629
No, you don’t?

534
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:47,920
No!

535
00:26:00,176 --> 00:26:01,176
Andres,

536
00:26:01,948 --> 00:26:07,193
if only you can teach that pup to operate
an oven or maybe balance our ledgers,

537
00:26:08,126 --> 00:26:09,312
then there should be no problem.

538
00:26:09,337 --> 00:26:12,879
Unfortunately, we really can’t take on
another responsibility in the bake shop.

539
00:26:13,245 --> 00:26:17,238
Don’t worry, we’re returning
her tomorrow to her owner.

540
00:26:18,479 --> 00:26:20,346
I’m not so happy about it, though.

541
00:26:20,371 --> 00:26:21,371
Of course, I understand.

542
00:26:22,252 --> 00:26:23,678
You know what, Andres,

543
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:26,500
think of it this way…

544
00:26:27,146 --> 00:26:28,726
when you love someone or something,

545
00:26:29,894 --> 00:26:31,214
it’s hard to let go.

546
00:26:32,638 --> 00:26:34,544
But when you know that
it’s gonna be for her good,

547
00:26:35,957 --> 00:26:37,310
we need to accept the fact.

548
00:26:37,767 --> 00:26:38,767
It’s hard,

549
00:26:39,402 --> 00:26:41,908
but that’s the way it’s supposed to be.

550
00:26:43,488 --> 00:26:44,488
Hmm?

551
00:26:45,172 --> 00:26:46,225
You love An-An?

552
00:26:47,027 --> 00:26:48,573
But you just saw her today.

553
00:26:48,598 --> 00:26:51,088
No, what I mean is in general.

554
00:26:51,113 --> 00:26:52,113
I mean it in a general aspect.

555
00:26:52,878 --> 00:26:53,878
That’s the way it’s supposed to be.

556
00:26:54,344 --> 00:26:56,444
Dad, I get it.

557
00:26:56,868 --> 00:26:58,048
I know it’s about Tash.

558
00:26:58,436 --> 00:26:59,436
Yes.

559
00:27:01,100 --> 00:27:02,120
But you know what, Dad,

560
00:27:04,765 --> 00:27:07,012
Anne told me something about An-An.

561
00:27:07,969 --> 00:27:09,189
If and when the time
comes that she gets lost,

562
00:27:14,592 --> 00:27:16,985
or when she doesn’t know
where to go,

563
00:27:17,948 --> 00:27:19,288
she can always find her way back,

564
00:27:20,529 --> 00:27:22,049
and that there are always
going to be people

565
00:27:22,074 --> 00:27:24,351
to take care of her
and be there for her.

566
00:27:24,376 --> 00:27:26,171
Even though your time
with Tash was only short.

567
00:27:32,134 --> 00:27:34,514
But, I just mean that
in a general sense.

568
00:27:45,188 --> 00:27:46,188
Hey, guys!

569
00:27:46,581 --> 00:27:49,574
What happened? Why do you look sullen?
You’ve got such long faces!

570
00:27:49,606 --> 00:27:52,086
Do you remember this
lost dog that we picked-up?

571
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:54,510
We’re returning her today.

572
00:27:54,923 --> 00:27:57,149
We’ve gotten so attached to her.

573
00:27:57,450 --> 00:27:59,588
Well, if you’ve already
gotten so attached to her,

574
00:27:59,612 --> 00:28:00,857
then don’t give her back!

575
00:28:00,882 --> 00:28:02,292
- He’s right!
- It’s the owners fault, they lost her!

576
00:28:02,317 --> 00:28:06,762
Did you know that there’s a
P5,000 reward if you return her?

577
00:28:06,787 --> 00:28:08,316
- That’s right!
- Why don’t you return her?

578
00:28:08,340 --> 00:28:10,485
- There’s a P5K reward.
- That’s the thing.

579
00:28:10,510 --> 00:28:11,971
Oh, here are the owners.

580
00:28:12,067 --> 00:28:13,086
Oh, she looks rich!

581
00:28:13,111 --> 00:28:14,790
We’re so sorry, we’re late.
We got stuck in traffic!

582
00:28:15,124 --> 00:28:16,601
- Oh.
- Rich, indeed!

583
00:28:16,778 --> 00:28:19,065
- Oh, she recognizes you!
- What?

584
00:28:20,313 --> 00:28:21,932
Thank you so much to you guys.

585
00:28:22,526 --> 00:28:23,759
What’s her name?

586
00:28:23,784 --> 00:28:24,784
Iskinepip!

587
00:28:24,797 --> 00:28:27,068
She was so skinny when
she was born,

588
00:28:27,092 --> 00:28:29,741
and she was the fifth
out of the brood, so fifth.

589
00:28:29,822 --> 00:28:31,743
Hang on… Iskinepip?

590
00:28:32,180 --> 00:28:34,207
Maybe my mother had
the same thought process…

591
00:28:34,535 --> 00:28:36,491
So, there are four of us,
and then

592
00:28:36,515 --> 00:28:38,140
maybe I was skinny too
when I was born.

593
00:28:38,165 --> 00:28:40,240
So… Iskini… port!

594
00:28:40,343 --> 00:28:41,616
Port! You’re right!

595
00:28:41,647 --> 00:28:43,304
Ah!

596
00:28:43,329 --> 00:28:47,234
Anyway,
here’s the reward we promised.

597
00:28:47,285 --> 00:28:48,285
Oh, no, no. Please keep it.

598
00:28:48,355 --> 00:28:50,022
We’ve agreed not to
take the reward.

599
00:28:50,059 --> 00:28:52,186
- I’ll take it, then!
- Yeah, yeah!

600
00:28:52,211 --> 00:28:56,787
People who do good
should always be rewarded.

601
00:28:56,931 --> 00:28:58,551
- We’ll take care of this.
- Count it!

602
00:28:59,210 --> 00:29:03,055
Kuya! We’ve already agreed on it,
we’re giving it back.

603
00:29:03,260 --> 00:29:04,493
You’re not going to accept the reward?

604
00:29:05,944 --> 00:29:06,944
Okay, here you go.

605
00:29:08,307 --> 00:29:09,307
Well, that’s a waste.

606
00:29:09,332 --> 00:29:11,505
We have another request though.

607
00:29:11,831 --> 00:29:14,638
May we visit her sometimes?

608
00:29:14,699 --> 00:29:16,332
That’s not a problem.

609
00:29:16,357 --> 00:29:18,631
We’ll give you our address
and contact information.

610
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:21,424
- Take care!
- Thank you so much!

611
00:29:21,449 --> 00:29:24,886
I’m gonna miss you, An–
I mean Iskinepip!

612
00:29:25,127 --> 00:29:26,671
Bye-bye, five thousand!

613
00:29:29,925 --> 00:29:31,894
- Are you really sure about this?
- Uh, we’ll go ahead, okay?

614
00:29:31,918 --> 00:29:34,040
I’m gonna have to go
and get my chihuahua trimmed.

615
00:29:39,578 --> 00:29:40,578
This way!

616
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:56,820
Ah, Tash.

617
00:30:01,850 --> 00:30:05,368
So… so… so…

618
00:30:07,436 --> 00:30:08,703
Wow, that took you a lot, Dad.

619
00:30:09,358 --> 00:30:10,984
Why don’t you just butt spell it?

620
00:30:12,328 --> 00:30:13,455
Um, Tash…

621
00:30:14,838 --> 00:30:16,138
S-O-R-I

622
00:30:16,163 --> 00:30:19,468
Oh, no shortcuts!
Do the correct spelling.

623
00:30:20,190 --> 00:30:22,940
- The correct spelling?
- Yeah, and spell it with your butt!

624
00:30:22,965 --> 00:30:25,697
- Butt spell?!
- Yeah, if you’re really sorry!

625
00:30:29,269 --> 00:30:30,883
Um, Tash…

626
00:30:33,521 --> 00:30:42,424
S-O-R-R-Y.

627
00:30:43,330 --> 00:30:44,510
I’m really sorry, sweetie.

628
00:30:45,067 --> 00:30:46,580
I’m sorry. Really, really sorry.

629
00:30:47,740 --> 00:30:51,295
I really am.
I’m so sorry. I’m sorry, my baby.

630
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:57,606
Stop! Wait , wait, wait, wait, wait!
Hold that pose! Hang on one second!

631
00:30:58,241 --> 00:31:00,928
Pose, and post!

632
00:31:00,953 --> 00:31:04,173
- Yay!
- Hashtag, together again!

633
00:31:04,290 --> 00:31:07,230
That’s perfect, together again!

634
00:31:08,293 --> 00:31:09,700
No, it’s just…

635
00:31:10,693 --> 00:31:11,693
You know,

636
00:31:13,314 --> 00:31:14,368
I have no valid excuse. But,

637
00:31:16,051 --> 00:31:18,007
please, excuse your Dad.

638
00:31:18,031 --> 00:31:20,783
It’s just that sometimes,
he can really be hard-headed.

639
00:31:22,702 --> 00:31:26,662
I know I haven’t told you,

640
00:31:28,503 --> 00:31:31,207
but you and Andres
are the reasons why until now,

641
00:31:31,231 --> 00:31:33,044
we’re still fighting

642
00:31:33,633 --> 00:31:34,940
for the life of this bakery.

643
00:31:35,392 --> 00:31:36,939
Because this is for you.

644
00:31:39,156 --> 00:31:40,156
Dad,

645
00:31:40,181 --> 00:31:42,163
you should know that
that’s also the reason why

646
00:31:42,187 --> 00:31:44,515
until now I haven’t accepted
Boss Eddie’s proposal.

647
00:31:45,273 --> 00:31:49,612
I still wanna give
my 100% to the bakery,

648
00:31:50,421 --> 00:31:51,908
for your and Mom’s dreams.

649
00:31:53,574 --> 00:31:54,574
You know,

650
00:31:54,868 --> 00:31:57,295
your Mommy and I have dreams.

651
00:31:58,811 --> 00:32:06,043
You and Andres also have your respective
dreams that we want you to fight for.

652
00:32:06,523 --> 00:32:07,523
We’re putting you first,

653
00:32:08,031 --> 00:32:10,477
because we know that
you’ll still want to help us out, right?

654
00:32:10,724 --> 00:32:11,724
You promise?

655
00:32:11,761 --> 00:32:13,028
You’re the priority.

656
00:32:13,099 --> 00:32:15,272
We’ll all fight for our dreams.
That’s a promise.

657
00:32:15,782 --> 00:32:17,409
Even if Eddie is my boss?

658
00:32:18,024 --> 00:32:19,024
If he’s your boss?

659
00:32:19,450 --> 00:32:20,770
Fine, okay.

660
00:32:24,632 --> 00:32:25,632
What is it?

661
00:32:33,175 --> 00:32:34,189
Oh, my heart!

662
00:32:35,819 --> 00:32:36,905
How are you all doing?

663
00:32:37,432 --> 00:32:39,044
Oh, it’s Eddie!

664
00:32:39,751 --> 00:32:41,537
One second, this is heavy.

665
00:32:41,597 --> 00:32:42,597
Dad, please hold this.

666
00:32:42,622 --> 00:32:44,536
What do you mean, Dad?! Ow!

667
00:32:45,842 --> 00:32:47,802
Uh, Tash…

668
00:32:48,501 --> 00:32:52,025
I heard from your co-workers
in Singapore that

669
00:32:52,609 --> 00:32:54,805
that’s your favorite song.

670
00:32:54,830 --> 00:32:57,970
I was hoping this would make
you give me your sweet, sweet yes.

671
00:32:58,909 --> 00:33:00,712
Because, the position that
you’re supposed to be getting,

672
00:33:00,737 --> 00:33:03,608
the person currently holding it
now has just retired.

673
00:33:03,803 --> 00:33:05,490
So, I really, really need you now.

674
00:33:06,002 --> 00:33:07,502
If I need to kneel down just to…

675
00:33:07,527 --> 00:33:10,689
Oh, no, no, wait, wait!
No, it’s okay!

676
00:33:10,769 --> 00:33:11,769
It’s fine!

677
00:33:11,912 --> 00:33:13,326
You look like you’re proposing!

678
00:33:13,577 --> 00:33:14,577
It’s all good!

679
00:33:14,751 --> 00:33:16,351
She’s accepting it, she’s accepting!

680
00:33:16,437 --> 00:33:18,215
- She’s accepting?!
- The job proposal!

681
00:33:18,492 --> 00:33:19,705
Oh my, thank you,
thank you so much!

682
00:33:21,085 --> 00:33:23,118
Thank you so much!
I’m so happy!

683
00:33:24,813 --> 00:33:28,219
Lola Maxi! Lola Maxi! Lola Maxi!

684
00:33:28,244 --> 00:33:29,541
I’m sorry,
I couldn’t help myself!

685
00:33:29,566 --> 00:33:30,566
Thank you, thank you!

686
00:33:32,271 --> 00:33:33,471
Stop touching her!

687
00:33:33,955 --> 00:33:35,168
Oh my!

688
00:33:37,447 --> 00:33:39,080
You really came back here?!

689
00:33:39,120 --> 00:33:40,393
You still haven’t had enough?

690
00:33:40,608 --> 00:33:42,982
Do you want a sucker punch
to your kidney?!

691
00:33:43,276 --> 00:33:45,956
- I’ll squeeze out your esophagus!
- What?!

692
00:33:46,013 --> 00:33:47,187
Come on, let’s split this stick in two!

693
00:33:47,212 --> 00:33:50,312
Ah, no, no, no. Don’t worry about it,
I’ll just go ahead.

694
00:33:50,337 --> 00:33:51,479
- Get out!
- Out, now!

695
00:33:51,504 --> 00:33:52,845
Okay, okay! I’m going!

696
00:33:52,870 --> 00:33:53,870
- Here you go again…
- One!

697
00:33:53,895 --> 00:33:54,895
Get out, now!

698
00:33:54,920 --> 00:33:57,548
- I am, I am! I’m going!
- Listen to Iskineport!

699
00:33:59,854 --> 00:34:01,127
Well? What are you waiting for?

700
00:34:01,822 --> 00:34:04,462
Aren’t we squaring up outside?!

701
00:34:04,715 --> 00:34:05,715
Let’s go!

702
00:34:06,592 --> 00:34:07,592
Oh, god!

703
00:34:09,367 --> 00:34:10,373
So, what now? …

704
00:34:10,804 --> 00:34:12,150
I thought you were fearless?

705
00:34:12,467 --> 00:34:15,981
Uh um… I, uh..
I have a sprain here.

706
00:34:16,940 --> 00:34:18,253
Maybe I should…

707
00:34:18,278 --> 00:34:19,990
But you sounded so dauntless just now!

708
00:34:20,983 --> 00:34:22,350
So, now you know!

709
00:34:24,075 --> 00:34:26,015
Well, that’s something!

710
00:34:26,186 --> 00:34:27,379
It seems like it was just yesterday!

711
00:34:27,769 --> 00:34:29,709
But now, here we are!

712
00:34:30,276 --> 00:34:31,276
Yes.

713
00:34:31,342 --> 00:34:33,495
Just like what we always say…

714
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:41,147
In struggles and in happiness,
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!

715
00:34:42,025 --> 00:34:44,099
Alright, let’s take a picture!

716
00:34:44,365 --> 00:34:45,865
Hold it, hold it, hold it!

717
00:34:46,878 --> 00:34:47,878
We’re here!

718
00:34:48,031 --> 00:34:50,324
- Oh! Hello!
- Hello, Pers Family!

719
00:34:50,349 --> 00:34:51,852
- Eddie!
- What’s up, Dad?

720
00:34:52,060 --> 00:34:53,740
No, no, I’m just kidding.
Brother…

721
00:34:53,765 --> 00:34:55,324
You really are something!

722
00:34:55,724 --> 00:34:57,763
Thank you, thank you,
but you had me worried sick!

723
00:34:58,801 --> 00:34:59,801
This guy!

724
00:34:59,982 --> 00:35:02,142
Did I get here too early?

725
00:35:02,247 --> 00:35:03,247
Oh, no, of course not!

726
00:35:03,252 --> 00:35:06,528
You’re just in time,
we’re about to take our family picture!

727
00:35:06,553 --> 00:35:08,007
Oh, I shouldn’t be a part of this.

728
00:35:08,228 --> 00:35:09,306
- Yeah, why should he be–
- Oh, no, no, you are.

729
00:35:09,331 --> 00:35:12,373
- Why?
- Because, you are Roman.

730
00:35:12,625 --> 00:35:14,545
You’re joining the family picture!

731
00:35:15,164 --> 00:35:16,744
Alright, okay, then!

732
00:35:16,769 --> 00:35:18,813
But, you come over here.

733
00:35:18,838 --> 00:35:20,272
- You, scooch over!
- Oh, sorry.

734
00:35:21,538 --> 00:35:26,257
We gotta do
Roman and I’s favorite pose.

735
00:35:26,282 --> 00:35:27,282
How is that?

736
00:35:30,212 --> 00:35:32,826
Embrace me, like this.
Put your arm around me.

737
00:35:32,859 --> 00:35:34,599
Like this? Just like this?

738
00:35:34,677 --> 00:35:36,543
Yes, and kiss my neck!

739
00:35:36,568 --> 00:35:40,631
Oh! Okay, okay!
As you take the picture!

740
00:35:40,917 --> 00:35:41,917
Okay, go!

741
00:35:42,012 --> 00:35:46,056
Pose, and… everybody compress!

742
00:35:46,251 --> 00:35:48,737
Pose, and post!
